sentences: Fellove was born on October 7, 1923, in the neighbourhood of Colón, Havana, Cuba.
In 1952, Fellove took part in some of the descargas (jam sessions) directed by Julio Gutiérrez at Panart Studios in Havana (released in 1956).
In 1952, Fellove took part in some of the descargas (jam sessions) directed by Julio Gutiérrez at Panart Studios in Havana (released in 1956).
In December 1955 he moved to Mexico with fellow filin songwriter José Antonio Méndez and joined the cha-cha-cha group Conjunto Batamba.
In 1956 he met Mexican promoter and head of RCA Victor in Mexico Mariano Rivera Conde, who gave him the nickname "El Gran Fellove", kickstarting his solo career.
In 1957, RCA Victor released an LP of Fellove's recordings entitled El Gran Fellove.
In the 1960s, Fellove switched from RCA Victor to Musart, releasing Watusi in 1966.

In 1979 he released his last album as a leader with his Conjunto Habana featuring Niño Rivera on tres.
In 2002 he recorded a cover version of "Walking on the Moon".
Fellove died on February 15, 2013, in Mexico City.
